title: Senior Embedded Software Engineer
description: FA.CDC is collaborating with global automotive OEM and Tier 1 on developing head units and MCU for global markets. You will be involved in various activities for Automotive market such as Researching and Developing Software Defined Vehicles with cutting-edge solutions for both Application and Framework/APIs development on a robust and reusable embedded environment. Moreover, it will be a precious chance to work with top experts of automotive industry to enhance both your technical knowledge and English.
requirements:
- Graduated from a university specialized in Electronics Engineering, Automatic Control, Automation, Computer Science, or related fields.
- At least 3-5 years of experience working with Android platform/Linux kernel
- Have participated in successful projects related to embedded software
- Demonstrated proficiency in C programming language
- Deep understanding about Android partition, Android boot process, Android Security model, Android GKI
- Deep understanding about AOSP build system
- Demonstrated proficiency in Kernel Driver development (Interrupt, Spinlock, multi-threading, …), Bootloader development, Device tree.
- Familiarity with Schematics, Datasheet
- Proficiency in using tools and software related to embedded software design
- Familiarity with using Multi Metter, Oscilloscopes, …
- Effective use of Git, Gerrit code review, CI/CD tools (Jenkin, QuickBuild, …)
- English: TOEIC 600+
- Soft skill: Strong Organizational, Analytical, Problem solving, Proactive, Teamwork, Independent work
- Have one/more of following skills/experience is an advantage:
- Holding specialized certifications, degrees, or relevant training courses.
- Experience in device bring up of In-Vehicle Information system (Audio, BT, Wifi, Camera, Sensors, …)
- Familiarity with Android boot processes (e.g. U-Boot) and bring-up experience
- Broad knowledge of Qualcomm, NXP, Renesas, …
- Experience in improvement Boot KPI, optimize resources (Disk, RAM,…)

title: Frontend Developer
description:
At NFQ, we focus on Scaling Business—helping companies grow, optimize, and transform through technology and strategic consulting. With 800+ experts across 8 offices, we don’t just build software; we partner with businesses to solve complex challenges, drive efficiency, and unlock new growth opportunities.
Unlike traditional outsourcing, our approach goes beyond executing tasks—we advise, challenge, and co-create solutions that enable businesses to scale effectively. Whether it’s expanding into new markets, streamlining operations, or driving digital transformation, we are committed to delivering impact that lasts.
Why NFQ?
🔹 Fairness – We treat our colleagues, clients, shareholders, and the environment with integrity and respect.
🔹 Entrepreneurship – We think like entrepreneurs, taking smart risks and turning ideas into real impact.
🔹 Excellence – We go beyond expectations to deliver results that truly make a difference.
We’re looking for a Senior Frontend Engineer to join DataBus, Shopware’s new event-streaming middleware. Nexus, its visual drag-and-drop workflow designer, is the frontend where merchants can seamlessly connect Shopware to any third-party solution without writing code. Built on a working MVP with React 18, Vite, and Tailwind, your team’s mission will be to transform this prototype into a production-grade application for thousands of merchants.
requirements:
- 5+ years professional Frontend experience with strong React + TypeScript in production. 
- Proven record shipping complex single-page apps (drag-and-drop, realtime data, or rich editors). Deep understanding of state-management patterns (selector memoisation, optimistic updates, cache invalidation). Performance and DX mindset: Web Vitals, bundle-splitting, dev-server tooling. 
- Accessible-first mentality WCAG 2.1 AA. 
- Familiarity with automated testing pyramid (unit > component > e2e) and CI gating. 
- Comfortable reading backend OpenAPI specs and modelling strong client typings. 
- Excellent English communication; ability to work 34 h overlap with CET.
